WEBVTT

00:57.809 --> 00:59.936
[PUPPIES WHIMPERING]

01:18.329 --> 01:20.457
[DOG WHIMPERING]

01:31.885 --> 01:34.012
[PUPPIES WHIMPERING]

03:00.557 --> 03:02.851
LAST ONE TO THE POND'S
A ROTTEN EGG'.

03:03.017 --> 03:05.019
FIRST ONE'S
A WORMY APPLE'.

03:07.272 --> 03:09.399
WHAT YOU DOING,
MISTER?

03:09.566 --> 03:11.651
NOTHING.
RUN ALONG, NOW.

03:11.818 --> 03:13.987
[PUPPIES WHIMPERING]

03:15.363 --> 03:17.574
WHAT YOU GOT
IN THE SACK?

03:17.740 --> 03:18.867
NEVER YOU MIND.

03:19.033 --> 03:21.327
I THOUGHT I TOLD YOU
TO RUN ALONG.

03:21.494 --> 03:23.496
MARY, HE'S GOT PUPS
IN THERE.

03:23.663 --> 03:25.540
YOU CAN'T DO THAT'.

03:25.707 --> 03:27.500
I TOLD YOU TO GET'.

03:27.667 --> 03:29.085
DO SOMETHING,
MARY'.

03:29.252 --> 03:32.171
YOU CAN'T DROWN THEM'.
YOU CAN'T'.

03:32.338 --> 03:35.133
NOW, GET'. BEFORE
I TAKE A STICK TO YOU'.

03:35.300 --> 03:37.594
GO ON'.

04:34.067 --> 04:35.818
[COUGHING]

04:40.740 --> 04:42.158
CAN YOU HEAR
ANYTHING?

04:42.325 --> 04:43.368
NO'.

04:43.534 --> 04:45.828
I HOPE THEY'RE NOT--
I CAN'T UNTIE IT'.

04:45.995 --> 04:47.538
LET ME TRY'.

04:48.873 --> 04:51.376
THEY'RE NOT MOVING'.
HURRY UP'.

04:51.542 --> 04:54.921
I'M DOING
THE BEST I CAN'.

04:55.088 --> 04:57.632
OH, GOD. LET THEM
BE ALL RIGHT.

05:00.677 --> 05:02.095
I GOT IT.

05:12.605 --> 05:14.983
[PUPPIES WHIMPERING]

05:33.501 --> 05:36.421
LAURA...

05:36.587 --> 05:38.506
THERE'S ONE MORE'.

05:39.924 --> 05:41.968
YOU SEE.

05:42.135 --> 05:44.178
IT'S NOT MOVING'.

05:46.180 --> 05:49.142
I CAN'T'.
I JUST CAN'T'.

05:59.777 --> 06:01.612
LAURA'.

06:01.779 --> 06:03.740
IT'S A ROCK'.

06:05.116 --> 06:07.076
A SILLY OLD ROCK'.

06:07.243 --> 06:09.078
[SOBBING]

06:24.302 --> 06:26.012
CHARLES, THE GIRLS JUST
WANT TO SEE THE PUPS

06:26.179 --> 06:27.930
ONE MORE TIME
BEFORE THEY GET TO BED.

06:28.097 --> 06:30.349
ALL RIGHT, BUT BE
REAL QUIET.

06:30.516 --> 06:32.477
THEY'RE JUST
GETTING SETTLED.

06:32.643 --> 06:34.771
Laura: WHAT'S JACK
DOING IN THERE?

06:34.937 --> 06:36.689
TRYING TO BE A WARM
FRIEND, I THINK.

06:36.856 --> 06:39.275
LOOKS TO ME LIKE
THE PUPS APPRECIATE IT.

06:39.442 --> 06:41.611
I BET HE THINKS
THAT HE'S THEIR MA.

06:41.778 --> 06:44.614
OH, LAURA, HE WOULDN'T
THINK THAT. HE'S A BOY.

06:44.781 --> 06:47.533
WELL, MAYBE HE
DOESN'T KNOW THAT.

06:47.700 --> 06:49.035
MA, DO YOU THINK

06:49.202 --> 06:51.412
THAT JACK KNOWS
THAT HE'S A BOY?

06:51.579 --> 06:54.040
I WOULD THINK SO.

06:54.207 --> 06:55.708
Mary: YOU SEE?

06:55.875 --> 06:57.126
Laura: WELL,
THEN, HE THINKS

06:57.293 --> 06:58.878
HE'S THEIR PA.

06:59.045 --> 07:01.547
I BET HE'D FEEL AWFUL
IF THEY EVER WENT AWAY.

07:01.714 --> 07:02.840
JUST A MINUTE,
YOUNG LADY.

07:03.007 --> 07:04.342
NONE OF
THAT FUNNY BUSINESS.

07:04.509 --> 07:05.760
WE TALKED
ALL THIS OVER.

07:05.927 --> 07:07.386
WE'RE GOING TO FIND
A HOME FOR THOSE PUPS,

07:07.553 --> 07:09.555
AND THAT'S THAT.

07:09.722 --> 07:11.682
YES, SIR.

07:11.849 --> 07:13.142
CAN WE BRING THEM
TO SCHOOL TOMORROW?

07:13.309 --> 07:15.186
THEN ANYBODY THAT WANTED
ONE COULD TAKE IT.

07:15.353 --> 07:17.146
I DON'T THINK
THAT'S BEST.

07:17.313 --> 07:19.482
YOU CAN TELL EVERYBODY
ABOUT THEM,

07:19.649 --> 07:21.818
BUT LET THEM ASK THEIR
PARENTS IF IT'S ALL RIGHT.

07:21.984 --> 07:23.027
YOUR MA'S RIGHT.

07:23.194 --> 07:25.071
SO PUT THE PUPS DOWN
AND GO OFF TO BED.

07:31.744 --> 07:34.580
THAT MEANS YOU, TOO.

07:34.747 --> 07:35.957
- GOOD NIGHT, PA.
- GOOD NIGHT, DARLING.

07:36.124 --> 07:37.959
- GOOD NIGHT, PA.
- GOOD NIGHT, HON.

07:38.126 --> 07:39.085
I'LL TAKE HER.

07:39.252 --> 07:40.711
Caroline:
THANK YOU, DEAR.

07:42.880 --> 07:43.631
PA.

07:43.798 --> 07:45.216
YEAH, HALF-PINT.

07:45.383 --> 07:47.593
I'M NOT GOING TO TELL
NELLIE ABOUT THE PUPS.

07:47.760 --> 07:49.595
IT'S YOUR CHOICE,
BUT I THINK THE OLESONS

07:49.762 --> 07:51.180
COULD GIVE A PUP
A GOOD HOME.

07:51.347 --> 07:52.682
OH, I KNOW THAT.

07:52.849 --> 07:54.934
I KNOW THAT NELLIE
WOULD FEED IT,

07:55.101 --> 07:57.603
BUT I DON'T THINK
SHE'D REALLY LOVE IT.

07:57.770 --> 07:59.480
YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN?

07:59.647 --> 08:02.191
I KNOW
WHAT YOU MEAN.

08:02.358 --> 08:03.442
GOOD NIGHT, PA.

08:03.609 --> 08:05.153
GOOD NIGHT.

08:10.449 --> 08:13.202
SHE REALLY LOVES
THOSE PUPS.

08:13.369 --> 08:14.453
YEAH.

08:18.040 --> 08:20.376
AND THEY'RE
SO CUTE.

08:20.543 --> 08:22.420
THEY ARE.

08:22.587 --> 08:25.381
I WONDER IF JACK
REALLY WILL MISS THEM.

08:27.091 --> 08:29.886
CAROLINE, YOU'RE
WORSE THAN THE GIRLS.

08:45.484 --> 08:46.360
GOOD MORNING, PA.

08:46.527 --> 08:47.820
GOOD MORNING,
HALF-PINT.

08:47.987 --> 08:49.447
YOU DRIVING US
TO SCHOOL?

08:49.614 --> 08:50.990
NOPE. EDWARDS
AND I HAVE TO MAKE

08:51.157 --> 08:52.575
A TRIP INTO SLEEPY EYE.

08:52.742 --> 08:54.785
WE WON'T BE LONG.
YOU READY FOR SCHOOL?

08:54.952 --> 08:57.288
YES, SIR.

08:57.455 --> 08:58.873
MAY I JUST BRING ONE
PUPPY TO SCHOOL

08:59.040 --> 09:00.333
JUST SO THE KIDS
COULD SEE?

09:00.499 --> 09:01.667
NO, MA'AM.

09:01.834 --> 09:03.127
IF THEY WANT TO SEE
THE PUPS,

09:03.294 --> 09:04.962
THEY CAN COME HERE
AND SEE THEM.

09:05.129 --> 09:06.505
I SUPPOSE.

09:06.672 --> 09:09.008
IT'S THE SANDERSONS'.

09:09.175 --> 09:10.676
Charles: GOOD MORNING.

09:10.843 --> 09:11.719
GOOD MORNING, CHARLES.

09:11.886 --> 09:12.678
LOOK WHAT WE GOT'.

09:12.845 --> 09:13.679
Boy: OH, HE'S SO CUTE.

09:13.846 --> 09:15.097
Girl:
CAN I HOLD HIM?

09:15.264 --> 09:16.599
SURE. WE GOT MORE
IN THE BARN.

09:16.766 --> 09:17.808
CAN I SHOW THEM, PA?

09:17.975 --> 09:19.101
SURE, GO AHEAD.

09:19.268 --> 09:21.020
Laura: COME ON.

09:22.146 --> 09:24.357
A NEW ADDITION TO
THE INGALLS FAMILY.

09:24.523 --> 09:25.608
WELL, JUST TEMPORARY,
THANK YOU.

09:25.775 --> 09:27.235
THE GIRLS ARE GOING TO
FIND A HOME FOR THEM.

09:27.401 --> 09:28.819
I'LL BE OUT TO YOUR
PLACE THIS AFTERNOON

09:28.986 --> 09:30.321
TO GET
THAT HARROWING DONE.

09:30.488 --> 09:32.323
OH, I WISH YOU'D LET
ME BORROW THE TEAM.

09:32.490 --> 09:33.824
I CAN DO THE WORK.

09:33.991 --> 09:35.618
NO, INDEED. YOUR HUSBAND
DID A LOT OF FAVORS

09:35.785 --> 09:37.328
FOR ME THROUGH
THE YEARS.

09:37.495 --> 09:39.121
THIS JUST GIVES ME
A CHANCE

09:39.288 --> 09:40.873
TO EVEN
THINGS UP A LITTLE.

09:41.040 --> 09:42.792
THANK YOU.

09:42.959 --> 09:45.044
IS CAROLINE GOING
TO TOWN THIS MORNING?

09:45.211 --> 09:47.296
YEAH, SHE'S ALL READY
SOON AS GRACE GETS HERE.

09:47.463 --> 09:48.547
I'LL SEE IF SHE
WANTS MORE COMPANY.

09:48.714 --> 09:50.258
I'M SURE SHE DOES.

09:53.886 --> 09:55.846
SURE WAS LUCKY YOU CAME
ALONG WHEN YOU DID.

09:56.013 --> 09:57.515
SURE WAS.

09:57.682 --> 09:59.100
I DON'T KNOW HOW
ANYONE COULD DROWN

09:59.267 --> 10:00.726
LITTLE THINGS LIKE THAT.

10:00.893 --> 10:02.395
I WISHED I WAS
BIGGER.

10:02.561 --> 10:03.938
I WOULD HAVE
TAKEN A STICK TO HIM.

10:04.105 --> 10:05.356
WISH WE COULD
HAVE ONE.

10:05.523 --> 10:06.232
YEAH.

10:06.399 --> 10:09.277
I WANT THIS ONE.
HE LOVES ME.

10:09.443 --> 10:11.070
ASK YOUR MA.

10:11.237 --> 10:12.446
I DON'T KNOW.

10:12.613 --> 10:14.824
MA'S GOT ENOUGH TO DO
LOOKING AFTER US.

10:14.991 --> 10:16.367
I DON'T KNOW IF SHE'D
TAKE KINDLY

10:16.534 --> 10:17.827
TO THE IDEA
OF CARING FOR A PUP.

10:17.994 --> 10:19.662
WELL, IT WON'T
BE A PUP FOR LONG.

10:19.829 --> 10:22.581
IT WILL GROW UP TO BE
A GREAT BIG WATCHDOG,

10:22.748 --> 10:24.583
AND MA WOULD LIKE
WATCHDOGS.

10:24.750 --> 10:26.836
THAT'S RIGHT, JOHN.

10:27.003 --> 10:30.089
WELL, I'LL TELL YOU WHAT.
ALICIA, YOU ASK HER.

10:30.256 --> 10:31.757
IT'S ALWAYS EASY
FOR YOU TO GET HER

10:31.924 --> 10:33.259
TO SAY YES TO STUFF, OK?

10:33.426 --> 10:35.469
IF I ASK HER,
CAN I NAME HIM?

10:35.636 --> 10:36.512
SURE.

10:36.679 --> 10:38.222
Laura: WHAT YOU
GONNA NAME HIM?

10:38.389 --> 10:40.891
MINE. I'M GOING
TO NAME HIM MINE.

10:44.812 --> 10:45.938
HEY, EDWARDS.

10:46.105 --> 10:47.189
HOWDY'.

10:49.775 --> 10:50.735
ARE YOU READY TO GO?

10:50.901 --> 10:52.236
ALL SET AND READY
WHEN YOU ARE.

10:52.403 --> 10:53.195
MISS SNIDER.

10:53.362 --> 10:54.530
GOOD MORNING, CHARLES.

10:54.697 --> 10:56.282
GOOD MORNING, GRACE,
MR. EDWARDS.

10:56.449 --> 10:57.700
GOOD MORNING, CAROLINE.

10:57.867 --> 10:59.493
MARY, RUN, TELL THE
CHILDREN WE'RE READY.

10:59.660 --> 11:00.453
YES, MA.

11:00.619 --> 11:01.620
WE'LL BE RIGHT WITH YOU.

11:01.787 --> 11:03.331
Charles:
SEE YOU AT SUPPER.

11:03.497 --> 11:05.458
HAVE A NICE DAY.

11:07.001 --> 11:08.794
HAVE A NICE DAY,
ISAIAH.

11:08.961 --> 11:11.297
NOW, DON'T GO DOING
THAT IN FRONT OF FOLKS.

11:11.464 --> 11:12.548
GO ON'. BYE'.

11:25.603 --> 11:26.854
IF YOU COULD
TAKE A LITTLE ADVICE

11:27.021 --> 11:28.022
FROM A FRIEND,

11:28.189 --> 11:29.440
I'D SAY MARRY
THAT WOMAN.

11:29.607 --> 11:30.775
THAT'S THE TROUBLE HAVING
FRIENDS.

11:30.941 --> 11:32.193
THEY'RE ALWAYS TRYING
TO GIVE YOU ADVICE.

11:32.360 --> 11:33.444
GIDDYAP'.

11:49.835 --> 11:50.836
WHEN YOU GONNA
ASK HER?

11:51.003 --> 11:53.172
I CAN'T ASK HER
UNTIL SHE'S ALONE.

11:53.339 --> 11:54.382
WE'LL BE IN
SCHOOL SOON.

11:54.548 --> 11:55.633
AND IT'LL BE
TOO LATE.

11:55.800 --> 11:57.009
Mary: I THINK YOU SHOULD
ASK HER NOW.

11:57.176 --> 11:59.011
IT'S HARD TO SAY NO
IN FRONT OF OTHER FOLKS.

11:59.178 --> 12:00.554
THAT'S TRUE
ENOUGH, MARY.

12:00.721 --> 12:01.889
GO ON.

12:02.056 --> 12:04.266
ALL RIGHT, BUT YOU
KEEP ON WALKING.

12:04.433 --> 12:07.144
I CAN'T LOOK SAD
WITH ANYBODY WATCHING.

12:07.311 --> 12:09.480
ALL RIGHT.

12:26.205 --> 12:28.290
Grace: YOU SHOULD'VE SEEN
THE LOOK ON ISAIAH'S FACE

12:28.457 --> 12:30.501
WHEN I KISSED HIM.
[WOMEN LAUGH]

12:30.668 --> 12:32.086
IN FRONT OF CHARLES.

12:32.253 --> 12:34.422
[WOMEN CONTINUE LAUGHIN]

12:40.302 --> 12:44.306
ALICIA, IS
SOMETHING WRONG?

12:44.473 --> 12:46.183
NO, MA.

12:57.069 --> 13:01.323
COME ON, NOW.
WHAT IS IT?

13:01.490 --> 13:03.534
IT'S JUST THAT I
WANT SOMETHING SO BAD,

13:03.701 --> 13:05.202
AND I'M SURE
YOU'LL SAY NO,

13:05.369 --> 13:08.581
AND IT'S MAKING ME
ALL SAD INSIDE.

13:08.747 --> 13:13.544
WELL, NOW, WHAT MAKES
YOU THINK I'LL SAY NO?

13:13.711 --> 13:16.755
'CAUSE JOHN SAID
YOU WOULD.

13:16.922 --> 13:19.091
YOUR BROTHER MAY BE
THE OLDEST,

13:19.258 --> 13:21.594
BUT THAT DOESN'T
MEAN HE'S ALWAYS RIGHT.

13:21.760 --> 13:23.345
YOU MEAN
YOU'LL SAY YES?

13:23.512 --> 13:25.806
YOU HAVEN'T TOLD ME
WHAT IT IS YET.

13:25.973 --> 13:27.266
A PUPPY. OH, MA,

13:27.433 --> 13:29.393
I WOULD LOVE IT
AND TAKE CARE OF IT,

13:29.560 --> 13:31.228
AND IT WOULD BE
A GOOD WATCHDOG

13:31.395 --> 13:33.230
SO YOU WON'T BE
AFRAID AT NIGHT.

13:33.397 --> 13:35.107
PLEASE, MA'.

13:35.274 --> 13:39.778
BEFORE I SAY ANYTHING, WILL
YOU ANSWER A QUESTION?

13:39.945 --> 13:41.113
YES'M.

13:41.280 --> 13:42.364
THE TRUTH.

13:42.531 --> 13:43.449
THE TRUTH.

13:43.616 --> 13:48.621
DID YOUR BROTHERS
TELL YOU TO ASK ME?

13:50.122 --> 13:52.291
YES'M.

13:52.458 --> 13:55.211
ALL RIGHT, THEN.
YOU MAY HAVE THE PUPPY.

13:55.377 --> 13:58.297
THANK YOU, MA'.
THANK YOU'.

13:58.464 --> 14:00.633
I CAN HAVE HIM'.
MINE IS OURS'.

14:00.799 --> 14:03.385
- HOORAY'. HOORAY'.
- GOOD FOR YOU'.

14:03.552 --> 14:07.640
HA HA HA'.

14:07.806 --> 14:10.601
OH, THEY'RE HARD
TO SAY NO TO.

14:10.768 --> 14:14.480
NOT HARD.
IMPOSSIBLE.

14:14.647 --> 14:16.941
OH, MY HUSBAND
WAS WORSE THAN ME.

14:17.107 --> 14:19.151
HE ALWAYS CLAIMED TO
BE THE STRICT ONE,

14:19.318 --> 14:20.819
BUT WHENEVER THEY
WANTED SOMETHING,

14:20.986 --> 14:22.363
THEY'D GO TO HIM.

14:22.530 --> 14:24.323
CHARLES IS
THE SAME WAY.

14:24.490 --> 14:26.784
IT'S BEEN HARDER FOR ME
TO SAY NO ABOUT THINGS

14:26.951 --> 14:28.244
SINCE THEIR
FATHER DIED.

14:28.410 --> 14:30.621
IT SHOULDN'T BE, I
SUPPOSE, BUT IT IS.

14:30.788 --> 14:32.414
IF I HAD A LITTLE
ONE LIKE THAT,

14:32.581 --> 14:33.999
I COULD NEVER SAY NO.

14:34.166 --> 14:35.668
OF COURSE, IT LOOKS LIKE

14:35.834 --> 14:37.336
I'M NEVER GOING TO HAVE
A LITTLE ONE LIKE THAT

14:37.503 --> 14:39.088
UNLESS I CAN GET
ISAIAH TO SAY YES.

14:39.255 --> 14:42.508
HA HA HA'.

14:50.891 --> 14:53.602
YOU CAN PICK UP THE PUP
ON THE WAY HOME FROM SCHOOL.

14:53.769 --> 14:54.562
Alicia: YEAH.

14:54.728 --> 14:56.188
Laura:
DON'T TELL NELLIE.

14:56.355 --> 14:58.190
Caroline: WAIT
FOR ME, CARRIE.

14:58.357 --> 15:00.859
WE'RE GOING TO PICNIC
AFTER CHURCH ON SUNDAY.

15:01.026 --> 15:02.611
CAN YOU BOTH JOIN US?

15:02.778 --> 15:04.280
I'D LOVE TO.

15:04.446 --> 15:05.864
WELL, YOU SURE
YOUR MENFOLK

15:06.031 --> 15:07.408
WANT ALL THOSE
CHILDREN AROUND

15:07.575 --> 15:08.951
ON THEIR DAY
OF REST?

15:09.118 --> 15:11.161
YES, THE MORE,
THE MERRIER.

15:11.328 --> 15:12.621
WELL, WE'LL
JOIN YOU, THEN.

15:12.788 --> 15:14.373
GOOD. SEE YOU SUNDAY.

15:14.540 --> 15:15.958
BYE-BYE.

15:19.628 --> 15:20.546
BYE-BYE, JULIA.

15:20.713 --> 15:22.172
GOOD-BYE.

15:32.558 --> 15:34.643
[BELL RINGING]

15:36.604 --> 15:38.397
Doc:
BE RIGHT WITH YOU.

15:45.904 --> 15:48.574
JULIA.
COME RIGHT IN.

15:48.741 --> 15:50.618
I DIDN'T EXPECT YOU
UNTIL NEXT WEEK.

15:50.784 --> 15:51.994
I KNOW.

15:52.161 --> 15:53.537
BUT YOU TOLD ME

15:53.704 --> 15:55.497
IF THERE WERE
ANY CHANGES...

15:55.664 --> 15:56.665
OF COURSE.

15:56.832 --> 15:58.417
SIT RIGHT UP THERE.

16:01.670 --> 16:04.256
IT'S PROBABLY JUST
SWOLLEN GLANDS.

16:04.423 --> 16:06.383
IT'S BEEN
GOING AROUND.

16:06.550 --> 16:10.220
IT'S MAKING ME
FEEL PRETTY WEAK.

16:10.387 --> 16:11.930
I DIDN'T WANT
TO TAKE A CHANCE

16:12.097 --> 16:13.349
WITH THE CHILDREN.

16:13.515 --> 16:17.227
I DON'T WANT THEM
MISSING ANY SCHOOL.

16:17.394 --> 16:19.438
YOU KNOW HOW IT
IS WITH YOUNG'UNS.

16:19.605 --> 16:21.440
FIRST ONE GETS IT,
THEN THE OTHER.

16:21.607 --> 16:23.525
THEN JUST WHEN YOU
THINK YOU GOT IT LICKED,

16:23.692 --> 16:26.320
IT STARTS ALL OVER.

16:27.946 --> 16:30.115
IT'S HAPPENING FASTER
THAN YOU THOUGHT,

16:30.282 --> 16:32.034
ISN'T IT, DOCTOR?

16:37.790 --> 16:40.334
YOU TOLD ME YOU'D
BE HONEST WITH ME

16:40.501 --> 16:42.002
NO MATTER WHAT.

16:42.169 --> 16:45.547
I KNOW. IT'S JUST
NOT THE KIND OF THING

16:45.714 --> 16:47.966
I CAN BE SURE OF.

16:48.133 --> 16:49.885
WELL, SURE OF WHAT?

16:51.053 --> 16:52.513
IT'S HOW LONG
I'VE GOT

16:52.680 --> 16:54.473
YOU'RE NOT SURE OF?

17:00.187 --> 17:01.647
CAN YOU GIVE ME

17:01.814 --> 17:03.148
ANY IDEA?

17:03.315 --> 17:05.734
[SIGHS]

17:05.901 --> 17:09.154
WHEN IT'S LOCALIZED TO
ONE CHAIN OF LYMPH NODES,

17:09.321 --> 17:11.156
I'VE SEEN PATIENTS GO ON.

17:11.323 --> 17:13.158
BUT IT ISN'T LOCALIZED.

17:13.325 --> 17:14.660
I DON'T WANT TO KNOW

17:14.827 --> 17:15.869
THE LONGEST I'VE GOT.

17:16.036 --> 17:17.496
I WANT TO KNOW
THE SHORTEST.

17:17.663 --> 17:20.708
I'VE GOT CHILDREN
TO PROVIDE FOR.

17:24.253 --> 17:26.672
A MONTH.

17:26.839 --> 17:28.257
A YEAR.

17:28.424 --> 17:32.386
A WEEK.

17:32.553 --> 17:35.139
IT COULD HAPPEN
ANYTIME, COULDN'T IT?

17:46.400 --> 17:49.445
WELL...

17:49.611 --> 17:51.822
I'LL BE DARNED.

18:09.923 --> 18:12.050
THANK YOU, DOCTOR.

18:18.265 --> 18:20.392
[BELL RINGING]

18:23.771 --> 18:25.355
[DOOR CLOSES]

19:15.697 --> 19:18.075
OH, YOU CERTAINLY
PICKED A HOT DAY

19:18.242 --> 19:20.244
TO BE
A GOOD NEIGHBOR.

19:20.410 --> 19:21.703
I'M ALMOST DONE.

19:21.870 --> 19:23.288
YOUR YOUNG'UNS CAME BACK
WITH ONE OF THE PUPS.

19:23.455 --> 19:25.374
THEY SAID YOU KNEW
ABOUT IT.

19:25.541 --> 19:26.458
I DID.

19:26.625 --> 19:28.126
GOOD. I JUST DIDN'T
WANT IT TO COME

19:28.293 --> 19:29.670
AS A SURPRISE TO YOU.

19:29.837 --> 19:31.630
SURE HAVING
A GOOD TIME WITH HIM.

19:34.299 --> 19:36.468
[CHILDREN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

19:42.933 --> 19:45.143
CHARLES...

19:45.310 --> 19:47.437
I'M GOING TO DIE.

19:50.858 --> 19:52.651
WHAT?

19:54.152 --> 19:57.281
I'M GOING TO DIE.

19:57.447 --> 19:59.783
I DON'T KNOW
HOW SOON EXACTLY,

19:59.950 --> 20:03.203
BUT IT COULD BE ANYTIME.

20:03.370 --> 20:06.582
DOC BAKER TOLD ME
THIS MORNING.

20:06.748 --> 20:10.335
I'VE HAD A FEELING ABOUT
IT FOR A WHILE, BUT...

20:12.170 --> 20:13.964
NOW I KNOW FOR SURE.

20:26.351 --> 20:30.939
THAT'S A HECK OF A THING TO
TELL A NEIGHBOR, ISN'T IT?

20:34.818 --> 20:36.486
IS HE--IS HE SURE?

20:36.653 --> 20:40.866
OH, YES, HE'S SURE.

20:41.033 --> 20:42.492
I'VE GOT A LOT TO DO

20:42.659 --> 20:46.413
AND NOT TOO
MUCH TIME TO DO IT.

20:46.580 --> 20:49.499
NOW, YOU KNOW A LOT
MORE FOLKS AROUND HERE

20:49.666 --> 20:50.834
THAN I DO,

20:51.001 --> 20:53.879
AND I'M GOING
TO HAVE TO FIND A HOME

20:54.046 --> 20:55.547
FOR THE CHILDREN.

20:55.714 --> 20:57.507
ANY SUGGESTIONS?

21:02.471 --> 21:05.766
OH, CHARLES,

21:05.933 --> 21:08.477
DON'T LOOK LIKE THE WORLD'S
COMING TO AN END.

21:08.644 --> 21:11.730
I NEED YOUR HELP,
NOT YOUR SYMPATHY, NOW.

21:16.944 --> 21:18.737
I'M SORRY.

21:20.739 --> 21:22.741
NOW, THEN.

21:22.908 --> 21:24.952
FIRST, I'VE GOT
TO LET IT BE KNOWN

21:25.118 --> 21:29.122
THAT I'M LOOKING FOR
A HOME FOR MY CHILDREN.

21:29.289 --> 21:32.501
I'M JUST NOT SURE
HOW TO GO ABOUT IT.

21:34.461 --> 21:36.546
WHY, I DON'T KNOW.

21:39.007 --> 21:40.717
I SUPPOSE I COULD TELL

21:40.884 --> 21:42.761
THE PEOPLE AT THE
CONGREGATION ON SUNDAY.

21:43.929 --> 21:46.807
OH, GOOD IDEA.

21:46.974 --> 21:50.852
AT LEAST I'D KNOW THEY
WERE GOD-FEARING FOLKS.

21:52.104 --> 21:54.189
BUT I'LL DO IT.

21:54.356 --> 21:56.566
I DON'T WANT ANYONE OFFERING
TO TAKE MY CHILDREN

21:56.733 --> 21:58.944
'CAUSE THEY
FEEL SORRY FOR THEM.

21:59.945 --> 22:02.698
THAT'S THE IMPORTANT
THING.

22:02.864 --> 22:04.491
PITY WEARS OFF PRETTY QUICK,

22:04.658 --> 22:07.369
AND IT'S A POOR
SUBSTITUTE FOR LOVE.

22:11.123 --> 22:14.876
I'M GLAD I LET THEM
HAVE THAT PUP.

22:17.587 --> 22:19.381
THEY DON'T KNOW YET.

22:23.635 --> 22:25.470
NO.

22:25.637 --> 22:28.390
I'LL TELL THEM TONIGHT.

22:35.439 --> 22:41.153
CHARLES, I NEED
A PROMISE FROM YOU.

22:42.904 --> 22:44.823
ANYTHING.

22:44.990 --> 22:48.535
WELL, I'M HOPING TO
HAVE ALL THIS WORKED OUT

22:48.702 --> 22:50.662
BEFORE MY TIME COMES.

22:50.829 --> 22:52.748
BUT IF I DON'T,

22:52.914 --> 22:56.501
I WANT YOU TO PROMISE
ME YOU'LL SEE TO IT

22:56.668 --> 22:59.254
THAT THEY FIND A PLACE.

22:59.421 --> 23:01.173
I KNOW IT'S
A LOT TO ASK, BUT--

23:01.339 --> 23:02.841
I PROMISE.

23:12.642 --> 23:14.394
THANK YOU.

23:24.029 --> 23:29.701
I THINK I'LL GO AND MAKE
A SPECIAL GOOD SUPPER AND...

23:29.868 --> 23:32.454
HAVE A TALK
WITH MY CHILDREN.

23:38.502 --> 23:40.837
I'LL SEE YOU SUNDAY,
CHARLES.

23:59.439 --> 24:00.273
MAMA'.

24:00.440 --> 24:01.775
MAMA'S HOME'.

24:26.591 --> 24:29.052
THERE, NOW.

24:29.219 --> 24:32.097
IT WILL BE NICE AND
COZY FOR OUR TALK.

24:32.264 --> 24:34.599
DID WE DO
SOMETHING WRONG, MA?

24:34.766 --> 24:37.394
NO, NO,
NOTHING LIKE THAT.

24:37.561 --> 24:39.187
BUT I WANT YOU
TO LISTEN

24:39.354 --> 24:40.939
TO ALL
I'VE GOT TO SAY

24:41.106 --> 24:42.899
AND NOT INTERRUPT,
ALL RIGHT?

24:43.066 --> 24:44.734
YES'M.

24:46.153 --> 24:50.282
NOW, YOU REMEMBER
WHEN YOUR FATHER DIED,

24:50.448 --> 24:51.783
AND I TOLD YOU

24:51.950 --> 24:53.869
WE'D ALL SEE HIM
AGAIN SOMEDAY.

24:54.035 --> 24:54.953
IN HEAVEN?

24:55.120 --> 24:57.080
SHH'. YOU'RE NOT
SUPPOSED TO TALK.

24:57.247 --> 25:01.751
THAT'S RIGHT.
IN HEAVEN.

25:04.421 --> 25:06.882
WELL, SOME OF US
ARE GOING TO SEE HIM

25:07.048 --> 25:09.342
SOONER THAN OTHERS.

25:11.261 --> 25:13.972
AND THE GOOD LORD HAS
DECIDED THAT...

25:15.056 --> 25:17.976
I'M GOING
TO SEE HIM VERY SOON.

25:23.273 --> 25:24.900
WHAT ARE YOU SAYING?

25:32.157 --> 25:35.452
OH, MY GOD, MA.

25:35.619 --> 25:37.746
JUST A MINUTE,
YOUNG MAN.

25:37.913 --> 25:40.290
YOU BE CAREFUL HOW YOU
USE THE LORD'S NAME'.

25:40.457 --> 25:42.709
AND I'LL HAVE NONE OF
THAT CRYING NEITHER.

25:42.876 --> 25:44.294
THERE'S NO REASON TO
CRY FOR SOMEONE

25:44.461 --> 25:46.087
THAT'S GOING
TO LIVE IN HEAVEN.

25:46.254 --> 25:49.007
YOU'RE CRYING FOR
YOURSELF AND NOT FOR ME'.

25:59.768 --> 26:02.896
THAT'S BETTER.

26:03.063 --> 26:05.023
NOW, I DON'T KNOW

26:05.190 --> 26:07.776
EXACTLY WHEN I'M GOING
TO BE WITH YOUR PA,

26:07.943 --> 26:09.694
SO WE HAVE TO MAKE PLANS.

26:09.861 --> 26:12.864
WE GOT TO FIND YOU
A NEW MA AND PA.

26:13.031 --> 26:16.409
I DON'T WANT ONE.
I JUST WANT YOU.

26:16.576 --> 26:20.705
CARL, THE LORD'S
MADE HIS DECISION.

26:20.872 --> 26:22.540
YOU LOVE ME, DON'T YOU?

26:22.707 --> 26:23.750
MORE THAN ANYTHING.

26:23.917 --> 26:25.710
ALL RIGHT, THEN.

26:25.877 --> 26:27.712
IF YOU LOVE ME,
YOU'LL HELP ME.

26:27.879 --> 26:29.673
WE'VE GOT THINGS TO DO,

26:29.839 --> 26:32.926
AND I NEED YOUR HELP.
ALL RIGHT?

26:34.052 --> 26:36.304
COME SUNDAY,

26:36.471 --> 26:38.223
WE'RE GOING TO CHURCH,

26:38.390 --> 26:42.811
AND I WANT YOU
FIXED UP IN YOUR FINEST,

26:42.978 --> 26:45.647
SPARKLING CLEAN AND PROUD.

26:45.814 --> 26:49.567
I DON'T WANT TO SEE YOUR
HEADS HANGING IN CHURCH.

26:49.734 --> 26:55.031
YOU'RE JOHN SANDERSON'S
CHILDREN...

26:55.198 --> 26:58.660
AND YOU GOT
A RIGHT TO BE PROUD.

27:07.377 --> 27:10.839
NOW, OFF TO BED.
I'LL TUCK YOU IN.

27:33.069 --> 27:36.489
WILL MY PUPPY GO TO
HEAVEN IF IT'S GOOD?

27:36.656 --> 27:38.283
OF COURSE HE WILL.

27:38.450 --> 27:40.118
THEN WILL
WE ALL BE TOGETHER

27:40.285 --> 27:42.037
FOREVER AND EVER?

27:42.203 --> 27:45.707
FOREVER AND EVER.

27:53.923 --> 27:55.967
NO TALKING
WHEN I SHUT THE DOOR.

27:56.134 --> 27:58.678
I DON'T WANT
SLEEPYHEADS IN CHURCH.

27:58.845 --> 28:00.722
OK, MA.

29:26.724 --> 29:28.184
CHRISTY'S DAD SAID
SHE COULD HAVE A PUP,

29:28.351 --> 29:29.853
AND I PROMISED HER I'D
BRING IT TO CHURCH.

29:30.019 --> 29:31.354
YOU CAN'T BRING A PUP
INTO CHURCH, LAURA.

29:31.521 --> 29:33.148
BUT SHE SAID SHE'D
KEEP IT IN THE WAGON

29:33.314 --> 29:34.482
TILL CHURCH WAS OVER.

29:34.649 --> 29:36.192
Charles:
SURE HER FATHER SAID
IT WAS ALL RIGHT?

29:36.359 --> 29:37.235
YES, SIR.

29:37.402 --> 29:39.571
HE SAID IT
RIGHT TO MY FACE.

29:39.737 --> 29:40.905
ALL RIGHT, THEN. YOU
MAY BRING THE PUP.

29:41.072 --> 29:43.741
THANKS. JUST ONE MORE
PUP TO FIND A HOME FOR.

29:43.908 --> 29:45.827
I HOPE IT'S SOON.

29:54.085 --> 29:55.587
MARY WILL BE READY
IN A MINUTE.

29:55.753 --> 29:57.630
NO HURRY.

29:59.424 --> 30:02.469
DO YOU THINK WE SHOULD
HAVE TOLD THE CHILDREN?

30:02.635 --> 30:03.887
I THINK IT'S BEST

30:04.053 --> 30:05.930
THEY HEAR IT
FROM MRS. SANDERSON.

30:07.432 --> 30:09.476
I SUPPOSE
YOU'RE RIGHT.

30:11.644 --> 30:14.272
I WANTED TO GO
SEE HER YESTERDAY.

30:16.274 --> 30:18.151
BUT I JUST COULDN'T.

30:20.904 --> 30:22.489
COME ON.

30:22.655 --> 30:24.449
SHE'S GOT A LOT
OF STRENGTH, THAT WOMAN,

30:24.616 --> 30:26.409
AND A LOT OF FAITH.

30:29.621 --> 30:31.831
I'LL GO PUT THESE
THINGS IN THE WAGON.

30:37.962 --> 30:40.465
Congregation:
♪ BY AND BY THE HARVEST ♪

30:40.632 --> 30:43.301
♪ AND OUR LABOR ENDETH ♪

30:43.468 --> 30:46.054
♪ WE SHALL COME REJOICING ♪

30:46.221 --> 30:49.933
♪ BRINGING IN THE SHEAVES ♪

31:03.071 --> 31:04.489
THANK YOU, REVEREND.

31:04.656 --> 31:08.409
IT'S VERY KIND OF YOU
TO GIVE ME THIS MOMENT.

31:15.500 --> 31:18.044
SOME OF YOU MAY NOT
KNOW ME.

31:18.211 --> 31:22.507
I'M THE WIDOW SANDERSON,
AND THESE ARE MY CHILDREN:

31:22.674 --> 31:27.679
JOHN JR., CARL, AND ALICIA.

31:27.845 --> 31:32.350
I'LL MAKE THIS
AS BRIEF AS POSSIBLE.

31:32.517 --> 31:34.519
I KNOW IT'S WARM IN HERE,

31:34.686 --> 31:38.356
AND THE REVEREND DID GET
A LITTLE LONGWINDED TODAY.

31:39.774 --> 31:42.277
IT'S REALLY VERY SIMPLE.

31:42.443 --> 31:47.365
I--WELL, I ALWAYS FELT
I WAS TOO ORNERY TO DIE,

31:47.532 --> 31:50.785
BUT IT SEEMS I WAS WRONG.

31:50.952 --> 31:52.620
GOD MUST HAVE FOUND
SOME GOOD IN ME

31:52.787 --> 31:54.956
'CAUSE HE'S CALLING ME EARLY.

31:58.793 --> 32:02.589
MY YOUNG'UNS HERE
WILL NEED A NEW HOME.

32:02.755 --> 32:06.009
I WON'T GO ON ABOUT
WHAT FINE CHILDREN THEY ARE

32:06.175 --> 32:09.596
'CAUSE AS THEIR MOTHER,
I'M A BIT PREJUDICED.

32:09.762 --> 32:13.308
BUT THEY ARE FINE STUDENTS
AND WELL-MANNERED,

32:13.474 --> 32:16.477
AS I'M SURE MISS BEADLE
HERE CAN TELL YOU.

32:17.979 --> 32:22.442
ANYWAY, I WANTED
TO LET IT BE KNOWN

32:22.609 --> 32:25.069
THAT THEY'LL BE
NEEDING A FAMILY.

32:25.236 --> 32:29.616
I'D APPRECIATE IT IF NO ONE
SAID ANYTHING RIGHT TODAY.

32:29.782 --> 32:33.411
IT'S NOT A DECISION
TO BE MADE IN HASTE.

32:35.163 --> 32:37.206
IT TAKES 9 MONTHS
TO HAVE ONE CHILD,

32:37.373 --> 32:39.208
SO FOLKS SHOULD AT LEAST
THINK ON IT

32:39.375 --> 32:41.502
A DAY OR SO
BEFORE HAVING 3.

32:43.755 --> 32:45.757
WELL, THAT'S ABOUT IT.

32:45.923 --> 32:47.800
THANK YOU.

33:19.290 --> 33:22.460
THAT CONCLUDES
OUR SERVICE FOR THIS SUNDAY.

33:24.629 --> 33:27.090
MAY GOD BE
WITH EACH ONE OF YOU.

34:26.607 --> 34:28.359
Julia: CHARLES'.

34:29.861 --> 34:32.488
WHERE ARE WE
GOING TO PICNIC?

34:37.535 --> 34:39.036
HOW'S ABOUT GROVER OAKS?

34:39.203 --> 34:42.749
SOUNDS DANDY.
FOLLOW US.

35:09.150 --> 35:10.276
[CHILDREN SHOUTING]

35:10.443 --> 35:11.986
Charles: HOW LONG
ARE WE GOING TO BE IT?

35:12.153 --> 35:14.572
YOU GUYS ARE
TOO QUICK FOR US.

35:14.739 --> 35:15.615
[SNAPS SUSPENDERS]

35:15.782 --> 35:16.866
WHOO'.

35:20.578 --> 35:22.497
Charles:
SOMEBODY GOT ME'.

35:22.663 --> 35:24.207
THOSE TWO MENFOLK

35:24.373 --> 35:26.000
DO HAVE A WAY WITH
CHILDREN, DON'T THEY?

35:26.167 --> 35:28.586
IT'S WHAT
THEY NEEDED TODAY.

35:39.305 --> 35:40.556
LAND'S SAKE.

35:40.723 --> 35:43.976
I'VE NEVER SEEN YOU
TWO SO QUIET BEFORE.

35:45.645 --> 35:47.021
COME ON. NO REASON

35:47.188 --> 35:49.816
WHY THEY SHOULD
HAVE ALL THE FUN.

35:49.982 --> 35:51.943
JULIA, DON'T YOU THINK

35:52.109 --> 35:55.238
IT'S A LITTLE HOT
TO BE PLAYING?

35:57.281 --> 35:59.700
WELL, THERE'S A...

35:59.867 --> 36:05.289
COOL BREEZE AND
A BLUE SKY AND...

36:05.456 --> 36:07.542
I'LL TAKE IT EASY.

36:07.708 --> 36:10.670
COME ON.

36:10.837 --> 36:12.088
I WANT THEM

36:12.255 --> 36:14.382
TO REMEMBER ME
LAUGHING.

36:14.549 --> 36:16.217
OH, JULIA.

36:21.681 --> 36:24.350
COMING, LAURA?

36:24.517 --> 36:26.602
NO, MA'AM.

36:26.769 --> 36:28.729
I'LL KEEP AN EYE
OUT FOR ANTS.

36:31.107 --> 36:32.984
ALL RIGHT.

36:34.402 --> 36:36.946
HERE WE COME READY OR NOT'.

36:42.201 --> 36:44.328
[CHILD GIGGLES]

36:46.330 --> 36:48.124
[ISAIAH SHOUTING]

36:59.594 --> 37:01.637
[LAUGHING]

37:02.597 --> 37:03.514
HO'. HO'.

37:03.681 --> 37:05.683
[ISAIAH
SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

37:05.850 --> 37:07.518
WHERE ARE THEY?
WHERE ARE THEY?

37:12.398 --> 37:14.025
OH'. OH'.

37:14.191 --> 37:15.693
OH, OH, YEAH.

37:15.860 --> 37:17.612
I THINK I GOT
A LITTLE ONE HERE.

37:17.778 --> 37:19.196
CAUGHT HIM. ALL RIGHT.
NOW ANOTHER ONE...

37:19.363 --> 37:21.449
[CHILDREN LAUGHING]

37:21.616 --> 37:22.867
GOT HIM'.

37:23.034 --> 37:25.369
I GOT BOTH. I GOT
'EM BOTH. ALL RIGHT...

37:25.536 --> 37:27.538
[LAUGHTER]

37:29.790 --> 37:31.334
Charles:
WHOA'.

37:31.500 --> 37:33.502
WHOA'.

37:40.426 --> 37:42.219
NOW'.

37:55.691 --> 37:57.234
WHERE YOU BEEN,
HALF-PINT?

37:57.401 --> 37:59.236
I'VE BEEN LOOKING
ALL OVER FOR YOU.

37:59.403 --> 38:00.738
IT'S TIME TO EAT.

38:00.905 --> 38:02.657
I'M NOT HUNGRY.

38:04.367 --> 38:05.743
NOT HUNGRY FOR
FRIED CHICKEN'.

38:05.910 --> 38:07.828
THAT DOESN'T SOUND
LIKE YOU.

38:09.789 --> 38:12.458
IT SCARES ME, PA.

38:12.625 --> 38:15.503
IT SCARES ME
BEING NEAR HER.

38:15.670 --> 38:17.296
WHY?

38:17.463 --> 38:20.591
'CAUSE SHE'S GOING
TO DIE, I GUESS.

38:20.758 --> 38:23.094
HOW OLD IS SHE?

38:23.260 --> 38:26.806
OH, 30 OR 40,
I SUPPOSE.

38:26.973 --> 38:30.434
MA'S IN HER 30s.

38:30.601 --> 38:32.103
THAT'S RIGHT,
SHE IS.

38:32.269 --> 38:33.688
YOU KNOW, HALF-PINT,

38:33.854 --> 38:35.731
YOU CAN'T SPEND YOUR
WHOLE LIFE WORRYING

38:35.898 --> 38:37.525
ABOUT DYING.

38:37.692 --> 38:40.152
IT'S NOT ME
I'M WORRIED ABOUT.

38:41.737 --> 38:43.406
JUST DON'T KNOW WHAT
I'D DO

38:43.572 --> 38:46.200
IF ANYTHING EVER
HAPPENED TO YOU OR MA.

38:47.994 --> 38:49.996
ANYWAY, NOTHING'S
GONNA HAPPEN TO US.

38:50.162 --> 38:51.956
NOT TODAY ANYWAY.

38:52.123 --> 38:53.457
NOW IF YOU SPEND
YOUR WHOLE LIFE WORRYING

38:53.624 --> 38:55.167
ABOUT SOMETHING
THAT'S GOING TO HAPPEN,

38:55.334 --> 38:56.669
BEFORE YOU KNOW IT,
YOUR LIFE'S OVER,

38:56.836 --> 38:58.796
AND YOU'VE SPENT AN AWFUL
LOT OF IT JUST WORRYING.

38:58.963 --> 39:00.798
[CHILDREN LAUGHING]

39:00.965 --> 39:02.258
HEY, YOU HEAR THAT?

39:02.425 --> 39:06.637
NOW, THAT'S WHAT
LIFE'S ALL ABOUT.

39:06.804 --> 39:09.598
LAUGHING AND
LOVING EACH OTHER...

39:09.765 --> 39:11.434
AND KNOWING THAT
PEOPLE

39:11.600 --> 39:13.978
AREN'T REALLY
GONE WHEN THEY DIE.

39:14.145 --> 39:16.856
WE HAVE ALL THE GOOD
MEMORIES TO SUSTAIN US

39:17.023 --> 39:18.858
UNTIL WE SEE
THEM AGAIN.

39:21.444 --> 39:24.280
IT'S HARD NOT
BEING AFRAID, PA.

39:25.698 --> 39:27.575
I KNOW, SWEETHEART.

39:29.368 --> 39:30.745
I KNOW.

39:32.955 --> 39:34.165
NOW, WHAT DO YOU SAY

39:34.331 --> 39:35.958
YOU AND I GO BACK AND EAT
SOME OF THAT FRIED CHICKEN

39:36.125 --> 39:37.543
BEFORE EDWARDS EATS IT ALL?

39:37.710 --> 39:38.794
ALL RIGHT, PA.

39:38.961 --> 39:40.046
COME ON.

40:05.404 --> 40:07.323
[KNOCK KNOCK]

40:11.702 --> 40:14.538
DR. BAKER,
COME ON IN.

40:14.705 --> 40:16.040
IT'S JULIA SANDERSON.

40:16.207 --> 40:17.917
SHE COLLAPSED EARLY
THIS AFTERNOON.

40:18.084 --> 40:18.959
OH, NO.

40:19.126 --> 40:20.461
REVEREND ALDEN'S
WITH HER NOW.

40:20.628 --> 40:22.880
SHE'S ASKED TO SEE
YOU AND CAROLINE.

40:24.965 --> 40:26.634
MARY'.

40:26.801 --> 40:27.843
WE HEARD, MA.

40:28.010 --> 40:29.595
KEEP AN EYE ON CARRIE
WHILE WE'RE GONE.

40:29.762 --> 40:30.846
YES, MA.

40:43.359 --> 40:44.443
GIDDYAP'.

41:04.380 --> 41:06.799
IS THIS IT?

41:06.966 --> 41:09.593
YES.

41:09.760 --> 41:13.722
I--I HOPE YOU WON'T TAKE
OFFENSE, REVEREND,

41:13.889 --> 41:15.641
BUT IF YOU'D JUST
READ THAT

41:15.808 --> 41:19.603
AND SAY A SIMPLE
PRAYER, I'D BE OBLIGED.

41:19.770 --> 41:22.148
WHATEVER YOU WANT,
JULIA.

41:23.107 --> 41:25.734
YOU'RE A FINE
REVEREND.

41:25.901 --> 41:27.903
BUT YOU DO TEND
TO GO ON A BIT LONG

41:28.070 --> 41:30.197
AT THESE KIND
OF THINGS.

41:30.364 --> 41:32.449
BREVITY WAS NEVER ONE
OF MY STRONG POINTS.

41:32.616 --> 41:34.410
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

41:34.577 --> 41:36.495
THEY'RE HERE, JULIA.

41:36.662 --> 41:38.455
I'LL BE OUTSIDE
IF YOU NEED ME.

41:38.622 --> 41:40.457
THANK YOU, REVEREND.

41:40.624 --> 41:42.418
OH, REVEREND.

41:42.585 --> 41:44.545
YES, JULIA.

41:44.712 --> 41:48.924
WHEN YOU READ THAT,
BE SURE NOT TO MUMBLE.

41:49.091 --> 41:50.885
READ IT LOUD AND CLEAR

41:51.051 --> 41:53.679
SO'S EVERYBODY CAN HEAR.

41:53.846 --> 41:55.347
LOUD AND CLEAR.

41:57.224 --> 41:58.976
YOU'LL HEAR ME.

42:24.376 --> 42:26.420
COME, SIT BY ME.

42:38.974 --> 42:40.809
THERE NEVER IS
ENOUGH TIME

42:40.976 --> 42:42.561
TO GET
EVERYTHING DONE...

42:42.728 --> 42:44.480
IS THERE?

42:51.070 --> 42:54.657
YOU MADE ME A PROMISE
THE OTHER DAY, CHARLES.

42:54.823 --> 42:56.492
REMEMBER?

42:57.993 --> 42:59.411
I REMEMBER.

43:03.040 --> 43:06.335
IT'LL BE UP TO YOU
NOW TO MAKE THE CHOICE.

43:08.420 --> 43:10.047
I KNOW.

43:11.674 --> 43:13.509
GRACE WILL TAKE CARE
OF THE CHILDREN

43:13.676 --> 43:17.137
TILL YOU MAKE
YOUR DECISION.

43:17.304 --> 43:21.100
IT WILL BE HARD FOR THEM
TO ACCEPT AT FIRST,

43:21.267 --> 43:24.186
BUT YOU'LL HAVE
TO BE FIRM WITH THEM.

43:26.772 --> 43:28.357
I WILL BE.

43:42.788 --> 43:45.666
LISTEN TO THAT RAIN.

43:47.876 --> 43:51.213
THERE WILL BE
A GOOD CROP THIS YEAR.

43:58.053 --> 44:00.889
SEND THE CHILDREN
IN NOW, WILL YOU?

44:15.821 --> 44:18.073
GOD BLESS YOU BOTH.

44:19.533 --> 44:21.118
GOD BLESS.

45:32.689 --> 45:35.109
Reverend Alden:
I WILL LIFT UP MINE EYES

45:35.275 --> 45:36.652
UNTO THE HILLS...

45:36.819 --> 45:39.279
FROM WHENCE COMETH MY HELP.

45:41.031 --> 45:42.658
MY HELP COMETH FROM
THE LORD,

45:42.825 --> 45:44.576
WHICH MADE
HEAVEN AND EARTH.

45:45.953 --> 45:48.664
HE WILL NOT SUFFER
THY FOOT TO BE MOVED.

45:50.666 --> 45:54.378
HE THAT KEEPETH THEE
WILL NOT SLUMBER.

45:54.545 --> 45:58.424
BEHOLD, HE THAT KEEPETH ISRAEL
WILL NEITHER SLUMBER NOR SLEEP.

45:59.550 --> 46:02.386
THE LORD IS THY KEEPER:

46:02.553 --> 46:06.890
THE LORD IS THY SHADE
UPON THY RIGHT HAND.

46:07.057 --> 46:10.727
THE SUN SHALL NOT SMITE THEE
BY DAY, NOR THE MOON BY NIGHT.

46:12.438 --> 46:16.275
THE LORD WILL PRESERVE
THEE FROM ALL EVIL:

46:16.442 --> 46:18.986
HE WILL PRESERVE THY SOUL.

46:20.612 --> 46:24.533
THE LORD WILL PRESERVE THY
GOING OUT AND THY COMING IN

46:24.700 --> 46:27.536
FROM THIS TIME FORTH,

46:27.703 --> 46:30.581
AND EVEN FOR EVERMORE.

46:30.747 --> 46:32.458
AMEN.

46:35.169 --> 46:40.591
JULIA SANDERSON ASKED ME
TO READ THIS TODAY.

46:40.757 --> 46:44.094
SHE WROTE IT TO ALL OF YOU,
LOVED ONES AND FRIENDS ALIKE.

46:59.776 --> 47:03.989
"REMEMBER ME WITH
SMILES AND LAUGHTER...

47:04.156 --> 47:08.118
"FOR THAT'S THE WAY
I'LL REMEMBER YOU ALL.

47:08.285 --> 47:10.245
"IF YOU CAN ONLY REMEMBER ME

47:10.412 --> 47:11.788
WITH TEARS,

47:11.955 --> 47:13.999
THEN DON'T REMEMBER ME AT ALL."

47:41.527 --> 47:43.612
LOUD AND CLEAR.
